The paper deals with the problem of reaching consensus in a distributed system, which is a classic topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the impact of different types of adversaries on the consensus problem, which is a common theme in computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes algorithms to solve the consensus problem, which involves analyzing the message complexity and time complexity of the algorithms, making it relevant to the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of partial orders in the consensus problem, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the use of consensus in hierarchical or dependable software/hardware systems, which is relevant to the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
